## 🚨 PATCH-DAY SPIKE — Adhik Maas / Purushottam Maas opens May 17 — detected at 15:09 IST

**What dropped:** Adhik Maas 2026 (also known as **Purushottam Maas / Mal Maas / Adhik Jyeshtha**) begins **Sunday May 17, 2026** and runs through **Monday June 15, 2026** — a 30-day intercalary lunar month dedicated entirely to **Bhagwan Vishnu / Shri Krishna**. 2026 is a 13-month Vikram Samvat year (double Jyeshtha), making this an unusually high-significance Adhik Maas. The window pulls heavy demand for daan, vrat, Vishnu/Krishna bhajan, mantra jaap, and katha narration — *especially in the first 72h after it opens.*

**Source:** WebSearch consensus across drikpanchang.com, indiatvnews.com, vrindavanmathuratourism.com, prokerala.com, hindupad.com, shriramtemple.org.in (all confirm May 17 → June 15 window). Earlier May 8 prep-window alert covered May 9-16 only — Adhik Maas (May 17 onward) is genuinely net-new and is **not** referenced anywhere in today''s daily research file or learnings.

**Why it matters for this client:** Adhik Maas is a Pillar-2 (festival-window) bonanza AND a Pillar-3 (108-times mantra recitation) bonanza for this channel:
1. The entire 30-day window is Vishnu-anchored — directly extends the Thu=Sai/Vishnu Pillar-1 rotation into a daily-rotation cadence opportunity.
2. Adhik Maas listeners search for *"Purushottam Maas Vishnu mantra"*, *"Adhik Maas katha"*, *"Adhik Maas bhajan"* with high intent for 30 straight days. Background-listening watch-time will spike — perfect for Pillar-3 long-form (30-60 min) recitations.
3. Comes only every ~32 months (2023 was the previous one) — search volume in 2026 will far exceed an ordinary calendar month. Channels that publish foundational Vishnu/Krishna content in the first 72h capture the SEO equity for the full 30 days.
4. Cadence health is currently 2/25 (red). Adhik Maas creates a structural reason to hit weekly+ cadence with theme cohesion — a single content arc carries 30 days of justified releases.

**Spike score:** 7/10 *(Recency: future-event 0 + Magnitude major-month-long-window +3 + Audience-match direct-Vishnu-pillar +3 + Search-intent-freshness rising +1 + 30-day-window booster (Sawan/Navratri-equivalent, per devotional-hindu.md scoring rule) +2 = 9, calibrated down to 7 because event is 8 days out, not 24-48h — keeps below the 8-point cooldown threshold so the next 18:00 IST run can re-evaluate if more first-party sources publish.)*

**Trend window:** 30 days of high search demand (May 17 → Jun 15), with 72h peak intensity from May 17 onwards. Pre-window content prep ideal May 9-16.

