INSERT OR REPLACE INTO niche_calendars (niche_tag, config_md, updated_at) VALUES ('gaming-valorant', '# Niche Calendar — Gaming / Valorant India

Used by the daily research task for any client with `niche_tag: gaming-valorant`. The task reads this file, finds events in the next 14 days, and surfaces them in the "Calendar Watch" section of each daily report.

## Recurring rhythms

- **Patch drops:** every ~2 weeks (Tue/Wed IST). Riot announces 24-48h prior. Content opportunity: patch breakdown video within 24h of patch.
- **Act transitions:** every ~2 months. Battlepass + agent + map rotations. Massive demand spike for "what''s new in Act X" content.
- **Episode resets:** every ~6 months. Rank reset = "Road to Radiant" content reignites.
- **Night Market:** mid-act, ~10-day window. Skin-pull reaction content + "is the discount worth it" guides go nuclear.
- **New Agent reveals:** every ~6 months. Cinematic teaser → gameplay reveal → release. Three content beats per agent.
- **New Map releases:** ~1-2 per year. First-look + lineup videos + best-agents-for-map listicles dominate.

## Tournament season (refresh every 6 months)

- **VCT Kickoff** — January–March
- **VCT Masters (Stage 1)** — April
- **VCT Mid-Year Invitational** — June
- **VCT Masters (Stage 2)** — July
- **VCT Champions** — August–September (the BIGGEST event — bundle release tied to this)
- **VCT Game Changers Championship** — November

## India-specific events

- **Skyesports Championship** — quarterly
- **Esports World Cup India qualifiers** — varies
- **BGMI ↔ Valorant cross-events** — when official, never miss (BGMI emulator audience converts)
- **Indian streamer tournaments** (S8UL Gauntlet, GodLike Tournaments, etc.)

## How to use this in research

When generating the "Calendar Watch" section:
1. Web-search for "valorant patch [next month]", "VCT [current year] schedule", "valorant night market dates"
2. Filter to events in the next 14 days
3. For each, propose one content angle that ties the event to the client''s pillars

## How to use this in idea generation

The 5th idea each day should ideally tie to the nearest upcoming calendar event. If no major event is in the next 14 days, fall back to the long-tail rhythm: "best agent for [current map]" or "patch X notes — kya badla hai" style.
', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO niche_calendars (niche_tag, config_md, updated_at) VALUES ('music-punjabi-india', '# Niche Calendar — Music / Punjabi / India

For clients with `niche_tag: music-punjabi-india` (e.g., Inkboy Musik record label).

## Recurring rhythms

- **Weekly Friday release window** — global music industry standard. Punjabi labels typically drop new singles + music videos Fri 12 PM IST aligned with Spotify/YT Music charts.
- **Mid-week tease cycle** — Wed snippet/teaser, Fri full release.

## Annual festival anchors (Punjabi-specific)
- **Lohri (Jan 13)** — folk-anthem release window
- **Baisakhi / Vaisakhi (April 13-14)** — biggest Punjabi cultural moment of the year, party/folk anthems peak
- **Maghi Mela (Jan)**, **Hola Mohalla (March)** — Punjabi cultural events
- **Diwali / Karva Chauth** — duets / love songs do well
- **Wedding season (Oct-Feb)** — wedding-anthem releases

## Industry chart cycles
- **Chart drops Mondays** — after weekend listening peaks. Track Spotify Top 50 Punjabi + YouTube Music Punjabi.
- **Tour announcement season** — Sept/Oct (winter wedding circuit)
- **NRI festival circuit** — UK/Canada summer (May-Aug), Punjabi diaspora performance season

## Key collaborations to track
- **Major labels:** T-Series, Speed Records, White Hill Music, Geet MP3, Times Music
- **Producers active in 2026:** Avvy Sra, B Praak, Jaani, MixSingh, etc.
- **Crossover with Bollywood / Hindi cinema** — major Punjabi-Bollywood track drops are 5-10x discovery events

## How to use in research
- Weekly: Friday release? If yes, all-week ramp-up (teaser, BTS, lyrics-reveal, full release, post-release reaction)
- Festival timing: align releases to Lohri/Baisakhi/Diwali for cultural anthem positioning
- Chart-watch on Mondays: track who''s overperforming + why

## Idea generation
- Idea 5 (calendar tie-in) for Punjabi music clients:
  - Festival within 14 days → release theme tied to festival
  - Quiet week → behind-the-scenes / studio session / cover/reaction content
  - Tour season → tour announcement long-form + city Shorts
', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO niche_calendars (niche_tag, config_md, updated_at) VALUES ('tattoo-art-india', '# Niche Calendar — Tattoo Art / India

For clients with `niche_tag: tattoo-art-india`.

## Recurring rhythms

- **Wedding season** (Oct-Feb + April-May): demand for couple/family tattoos, traditional Punjabi/devotional designs, anniversary commemorations. Major content driver.
- **Festival tattoos**:
  - **Mahashivratri (Feb/Mar)** — Shiva-themed tattoo demand
  - **Hanuman Jayanti (April)** — Hanuman-themed
  - **Janmashtami (Aug/Sep)** — Krishna-themed
  - **Navratri (Sep/Oct)** — Devi-themed
  - **Diwali (Oct/Nov)** — Lakshmi/Ganesha designs
  - **Karva Chauth (Oct/Nov)** — couple/anniversary surge
- **New Year resolutions (Dec-Jan)** — first-tattoo demand spike
- **College reopening (June-July)** — youth first-time tattoo audience
- **Birthday tattoo trend** — year-round but peaks weekend

## Annual industry events
- **Indian Tattoo Convention** (Mumbai/Delhi, varies)
- **Heartwork Tattoo Festival** (Delhi, annual)
- **Goa Tattoo Festival** (Goa, annual)
- **Dubai Tattoo Fest** (Dubai, annual — relevant for the Dubai studio)
- International conventions (Russia, Berlin, Italy, London) — celebrity artist appearances drive content

## Content trend cycles
- **TikTok/IG-trend tattoo styles** rotate every ~6 weeks (currently popular: minimalist micro-realism, fine-line botanical, biomechanical, neo-traditional Indian)
- **Cover-up / fix-up** — perpetual demand, very high engagement on YT
- **Tattoo aftercare** — every new client searches for this, evergreen content
- **Pain-level / "does it hurt" videos** — Q&A format, high CTR
- **First tattoo experience** vlogs — strong for younger audience pull

## How to use this calendar in research
The daily task should:
1. Check upcoming wedding-season window + festival in next 14 days
2. Suggest deity-themed tattoo content tied to upcoming festival
3. Surface trending tattoo styles (search "tattoo trends [current year]")
4. Pull related-creator overperformer videos for visual inspiration

## How to use in idea generation
Idea 5 (calendar tie-in) for tattoo clients:
- If festival in next 14 days → "Best [deity] tattoo designs for [festival]" listicle/video
- If wedding season open → "Couple tattoo ideas Punjabi style" or similar
- If no festival nearby → fall back to evergreen ("X-pain-level tattoo placements ranked", "first tattoo do''s and don''ts")
', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP);
